Task 1:
Develop a mobile application that allows users to track their daily water intake and sends reminders throughout the day. The app should include data visualization and goal-setting features.

Summary:
Overview
- Mobile app to track daily water intake and send reminders
- Includes data visualization and goal-setting

Core features
- Quick water logging (preset + custom amounts)
- Daily/weekly/monthly intake charts
- Custom daily goal setup
- Scheduled and smart reminders
- Streaks and progress summary
- Onboarding and initial goal suggestion
- User settings and notification control
- Data export (CSV) and backup option

User stories
- Log water with one tap
- Receive reminders at chosen times
- Adjust daily goal and cup size
- View intake trends and streaks
- Pause reminders (do not disturb)
- Restore data on new device

Primary screens
- Onboarding / set goal
- Home / quick log + today progress
- Add log / history list
- Charts / analytics screen
- Reminders / schedule screen
- Settings / profile / export

Data model (local)
- User: id, dailyGoal, cupSize, timezone, preferences
- LogEntry: id, timestamp, amount
- Reminder: id, time, repeatPattern, enabled
- SyncMeta: lastSync, backupId

Notifications
- Local scheduled notifications per user times
- Smart reminder logic (based on remaining intake and wake/sleep)
- Snooze and adaptive frequency
- Respect system do-not-disturb and user permissions

Data visualization
- Today progress ring
- Hourly timeline for today
- 7/30/90-day line and bar charts
- Average daily intake and goal attainment %
- Highlight streaks and longest streak

Goal-setting
- Default goal by weight/age suggestion
- Manual goal edits
- Adaptive goal suggestions based on usage trends

Architecture options
- Single-device (local only): SQLite/Realm, no backend
- Cloud-sync: REST API + auth, PostgreSQL or Firebase
- Cross-platform: React Native or Flutter

Tech stack suggestions
- Frontend: React Native + TypeScript OR Flutter
- Storage: SQLite (WatermelonDB/Room) or Realm
- Notifications: native push/local (APNs/Firebase Messaging/local)
- Backend (optional): Firebase Firestore or Node.js + PostgreSQL
- Charts: Recharts/MPAndroidChart/Charts (iOS) / FL Chart

Third-party libs
- Local DB: Realm or SQLite wrapper
- Charts: Victory/React Native SVG Charts or FL Chart
- Notifications: react-native-push-notification or flutter_local_notifications
- Analytics: Firebase Analytics (optional)

Security & privacy
- Store minimal personal data
- Optional passcode/biometric lock
- GDPR-compliant export/delete data
- Encrypted local backups

Testing & QA
- Unit tests for core logic
- Integration tests for notifications and storage
- Usability testing for onboarding and reminders
- Device compatibility for iOS/Android

Milestones & timeline (MVP)
- Week 1: Requirements, wireframes, setup
- Week 2: Logging, local storage, home UI
- Week 3: Reminders, notification flows
- Week 4: Charts, goal-setting, settings
- Week 5: Polish, QA, app store prep
- Optional +2â€“3 weeks for cloud sync & accounts

Acceptance criteria
- Log added within 3 taps
- Reminders delivered on schedule
- Charts reflect logged data accurately
- Goal adjustable and progress updates in real time

Deliverables
- Installable APK/IPAs (or builds)
- Source code repo with README
- Design assets and wireframes
- Test cases and deployment instructions

Next steps
- Choose platform (React Native or Flutter)
- Confirm MVP feature list and timeline
- Provide design preferences and branding assets

